message.content: {"id": "45145", "title": "Bug 45145: Second window comes to front when using first", "description": "When using two Eclipse windows and switching from another application to one Eclipse window, clicking on a docked view or perspective causes the other window to come to the front, covering the windows of other applications.", "OB": "When switching from another application to one Eclipse window and clicking on a docked view or perspective, the other Eclipse window comes to the front, covering the windows of other applications", "EB": "When switching from another application to one Eclipse window and clicking on a docked view or perspective, the other Eclipse window should remain in the background and not cover the windows of other applications", "SR": "Ensure that when switching from another application to one Eclipse window and clicking on a docked view or perspective, the other Eclipse window does not come to the front and covers the windows of other applications"}
